HEADWORD: Prickwood
<hw>Prick"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A shrub (<spn>Euonymus Europ⟦ae⟧us</spn>); -- so named from the use
of its wood for goads, skewers, and shoe pegs. Called also
<altname>spindle tree</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pricky</ent>⟦br⟧
